-- Ausone Leads Christie’s London Wine Sale With Margaux, Mouton
-- B y   G u y   C o l l i n s
-- 2012-10-18T18:19:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-18/ausone-leads-christie-s-london-wine-sale-with-margaux-mouton.html
A case of  Chateau Ausone  2000 from
Bordeaux’s Saint-Emilion region fetched the top price of 9,200
pounds ($14,800) at a Christie’s International Plc wine sale in
 London  today, the auction house said in an e-mailed statement.  A case of  Chateau Margaux  1990 took second slot, fetching
7,475 pounds, while 12 bottles of Chateau Mouton-Rothschild 1982
sold for 6,900 pounds, Christie’s said. The auction fetched a
total 492,000 pounds, with 99 percent of the lots selling.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Guy Collins in London at 
